summary: Completed comprehensive backend testing of Pro-Tech Diagnostic Behavior implementation with 11 RV system procedures. All 504 existing tests pass, confirming the diagnostic system works correctly.
passed_tests: detectSystem: identifies water_pump, furnace, roof_ac, lp_gas, refrigerator, slide_out, leveling, inverter_converter, electrical_12v, electrical_ac, consumer_appliance
detectSystem: returns null for unknown system
getProcedure: returns correct procedure for each system with unique step IDs
getNextStep: returns first step with no completions, skips completed, respects prerequisites
LP Gas: pressure test (lpg_2) precedes ignition (lpg_5) with correct prerequisite chain
mapInitialMessageToSteps: maps voltage/ground readings to completed steps from initial message
mapInitialMessageToSteps: does not over-map ambiguous messages
buildProcedureContext: shows ACTIVE DIAGNOSTIC PROCEDURE, completed steps, next step, prevents cross-system drift
initializeCase: initializes procedure from first message, pre-completes steps, does not re-initialize
processUserMessage: tracks completed steps and unable-to-verify steps in procedure-aware mode
shouldPivot: returns true for key findings (missing blade, seized motor, cracked housing), false otherwise
Falls back to legacy topic tracking when no procedure matches
detectAlreadyAnswered: recognizes 'already checked', 'already told you', 'already answered' patterns
detectUnableToVerify: recognizes 'don't know', 'can't check', 'unable to verify' patterns
detectKeyFinding: detects pivot triggers like missing fan blade, blower wheel damage, seized motor
All 11 RV system procedures properly defined with structured steps and prerequisites
success_percentage: backend: 100% (all 504 tests pass), frontend: N/A (backend-only testing)
